### Sequential API

The Sequential API is the simplest way to build models in Keras. Layers are
stacked in a linear fashion—one input, one output—making it ideal for simple
architectures.

#### Figure 3.4 — Sequential model diagram
<p align='left'><img src='./figure/figure3.4.png' width='60%'></p>

---

### Functional API

The Functional API allows the construction of more flexible and complex
networks. It supports multi-input and multi-output models, branching layers,
and shared layer components.

#### Figure 3.5 — Functional API model flow
<p align='left'><img src='./figure/figure3.5.png' width='60%'></p>

---

### Sub-classing API

The Sub-classing API gives full control over model behavior by allowing the
developer to define custom Python classes. This is useful for highly customized
architectures or research-oriented models.

